#Approach:

**Hinglish quick revision:**

Tumhara code almost sahi hai, but `kthnodeFinder()` mein issue hai.
Agar remaining nodes `k` se kam hue, to `temp = temp.next` karte karte `temp` null ho jayega aur NPE aa sakta hai.
Bas wahi fix karna tha by checking:

`if(temp == null) return null;`

Baaki logic sahi hai:

* pehle `kthNode` find kiya
* group ko tod diya using `kthNode.next = null`
* group reverse kiya
* previous part se connect kiya
* next group pe move kar gaye

Time Complexity: **O(n)**
Space Complexity: **O(k)** recursion stack for each group


#Code:

/**
 * Definition for singly-linked list.
 * public class ListNode {
 *     int val;
 *     ListNode next;
 *     ListNode() {}
 *     ListNode(int val) { this.val = val; }
 *     ListNode(int val, ListNode next) { this.val = val; this.next = next; }
 * }
 */
class Solution {

    private ListNode reverse(ListNode head){
        if(head == null || head.next == null){
            return head;
        }
        ListNode newHead = reverse(head.next);
        ListNode front = head.next;
        front.next = head;
        head.next = null;
        return newHead;
    }

    private ListNode kthnodeFinder(ListNode x, int k){
        ListNode temp = x;
        for(int i=1; i<k; i++){
            if(temp == null) return null;
            temp = temp.next;
        }
        return temp;
    }

    public ListNode reverseKGroup(ListNode head, int k) {

        ListNode temp = head;
        ListNode prevNode = null;
        while(temp != null){
            ListNode kthNode = kthnodeFinder(temp, k);
            if(kthNode == null){
                if(prevNode != null){
                    prevNode.next = temp;
                }
                break;
            }
            ListNode nextNode = kthNode.next;
            kthNode.next = null;

            reverse(temp);
            if(temp == head){
                //first group
                head = kthNode;
            }
            else{
                //other group
                prevNode.next = kthNode;
            }
            prevNode = temp;
            temp = nextNode;
        }
        return head;
    }
}
